Prerequisites:
    1. Programming language used : go1.20.3
        Install golang [Refer for help : https://go.dev/doc/install]

    2. DataBase used : Mongo DB - 7.0.7
        Install mongo DB [Refer for help : https://www.mongodb.com/docs/manual/installation/]

    3. Currently we are using gmail for sending Emails. Please generate a app password from gmail and set it in os.env under the key : password.
        Refer for help : https://medium.com/@piusrestiantoro02/how-to-generate-a-gmail-app-password-0e71cd41fd3c

Steps to run the project:

1. Download the project using the command "git clone git@github.com:vaibhavgvk08/TigerHall-Kittens.git"

2. Navigate to the root directory of the project in your terminal or editor.

3. Run the following command to initialize Go modules:
   ```
   go mod init github.com/vaibhavgvk08/tigerhall-kittens
   ```

4. Run the following command to ensure Go modules are tidy:
   ```
   go mod tidy
   ```

5. Finally, run the following command to install dependencies:
   ```
   go mod download
   ```
6. After all dependency modules are successfully installed, run the following command to start the server :
   ```
   go run server.go
   ```